Application Example: Temperature Sensor (LM35)

LM35 outputs 10 mV per °C referenced to ground. Counts → volts → °C.

float lm35_read_celsius(void)
{
  uint16_t raw = hal_read_adc_channel(TEMP_CH);
  float volts = (raw / 4095.0f) * 3.3f; // 0–3.3 V span
  return volts * 100.0f;               // 10 mV per °C
}

Application Example: Light Sensor (LDR)

Use a divider with known resistor R_FIXED. Solve for the LDR resistance, then map to lux.

float ldr_read_lux(void)
{
  uint16_t raw = hal_read_adc_channel(LDR_CH);
  float v = (raw / 4095.0f) * 3.3f;
  float r_ldr = (v * R_FIXED) / (3.3f - v);
  return ldr_resistance_to_lux(r_ldr);
}

