Application Example: Pressure Sensor

Sensors such as MPX5010 output 0.5–4.5 V for their span. Subtract offset and scale to kPa.

float pressure_kpa(void)
{
  uint16_t raw = hal_read_adc_channel(PRESS_CH);
  float volts = (raw / 4095.0f) * 3.3f;
  const float sensor_span_kpa = 100.0f; // datasheet value (0.5–4.5 V span)
  return (volts - 0.5f) * (sensor_span_kpa / 4.0f);
}

Application Example: Soil Moisture Probe

Calibrate wet/dry counts, then map to percentage for irrigation logic.

uint8_t soil_moisture_pct(void)
{
  uint16_t raw = hal_read_adc_channel(SOIL_CH);
  if (raw &lt; wet_counts) raw = wet_counts;
  if (raw &gt; dry_counts) raw = dry_counts;
  return (uint8_t)(100U * (dry_counts - raw) / (dry_counts - wet_counts));
}

Application Example: Microphone Envelope

Sample a block and track the peak (or RMS) to feed VU meters or trigger detection.

uint16_t mic_peak(void)
{
  uint16_t peak = 0;
  for (int i = 0; i &lt; 256; ++i)
  {
    uint16_t s = hal_read_adc_channel(MIC_CH);
    if (s &gt; peak) peak = s;
  }
  return peak;
}

Application Example: Battery Voltage Monitor

With a resistor divider (R1 to battery, R2 to ground) scale the ADC voltage back to pack volts.

float battery_voltage(void)
{
  uint16_t raw = hal_read_adc_channel(BATT_CH);
  float v_adc = (raw / 4095.0f) * 3.3f;
  return v_adc * (R1 + R2) / R2;
}

