Example: BME280 I2C Burst Read
Reading Temperature & Pressure Data
/* BME280 I2C Address (SDO=GND) -&gt; 0x76. Shift left for HAL -&gt; 0xEC */
#define BME280_ADDR (0x76 &lt;&lt; 1)

/* Burst read 6 bytes starting from 0xF7 (press_msb) */
uint8_t regAddr = 0xF7; 
uint8_t rawData[6]; // Buffer for Pressure (3 bytes) + Temp (3 bytes)

/* Step 1: Send starting register address */
HAL_I2C_Master_Transmit(&hi2c1, BME280_ADDR, &regAddr, 1, HAL_MAX_DELAY);

/* Step 2: Read 6 bytes sequentially */
HAL_I2C_Master_Receive(&hi2c1, BME280_ADDR, rawData, 6, HAL_MAX_DELAY);

/* Step 3: Combine bytes (MSB, LSB, XLSB) */
int32_t adc_P = (rawData[0] &lt;&lt; 12) | (rawData[1] &lt;&lt; 4) | (rawData[2] &gt;&gt; 4);
int32_t adc_T = (rawData[3] &lt;&lt; 12) | (rawData[4] &lt;&lt; 4) | (rawData[5] &gt;&gt; 4);

Note: In HAL_I2C_Master_Receive, you do not need to manually set the LSB of the address to 1. The HAL function automatically handles the Read/Write bit.

