DMA Interrupts

Identify DMA interrupt type by checking DMA interrupt status registers (LISR and HISR).
Each DMA stream can generate:

Transfer finished (TC)
Half-transfer
Transfer error

Interrupts are enabled through interrupt enable bits in SxCR.

// Enable the transfer complete interrupt
DMA2_Stream0-&gt;CR |= DMA_SxCR_TCIE;

// Disable the half transfer interrupt (commonly written as: &= ~DMA_SxCR_HTIE)
DMA2_Stream0-&gt;CR &= -DMA_SxCR_HTIE;

// Set the priority as the most urgent
NVIC_SetPriority(DMA2_Stream0_IRQn, 0);

// Enable NVIC interrupt
NVIC_EnableIRQ(DMA2_Stream0_IRQn);

DMA Interrupt Handler (Example)

Clear interrupts by writing 1 to the corresponding bit in the interrupt clear registers (LIFCR / HIFCR).

void DMA2_Stream0_IRQHandler(void){
  if ((DMA2-&gt;LISR & DMA_LISR_TCIF0) == DMA_LISR_TCIF0){ // transfer complete
    DMA2-&gt;LIFCR |= DMA_LIFCR_CTCIF0; // Clear flag TCIF by writing 1 to it
    ...
  }
  if ((DMA2-&gt;LISR & DMA_LISR_HTIF0) == DMA_LISR_HTIF0){ // half transfer
    DMA2-&gt;LIFCR |= DMA_LIFCR_CHTIF0; // Clear flag HTIF by writing 1 to it
    ...
  }
  if ((DMA2-&gt;LISR & DMA_LISR_TEIF0) == DMA_LISR_TEIF0){ // transfer error
    DMA2-&gt;LIFCR |= DMA_LIFCR_CTEIF0; // Clear flag TEIF by writing 1 to it
    ...
  }
}
